x4freetext: -THE NEUTRON INDUCED FISSION CROSS SECTION OF
235-U IN THE ENERGY REGION FROM 0.008EV TO 30KEV-.
30 METER FLIGHT STATION OF THE CBNM LINAC
BOMBARDMENT OF THE MERCURY COOLED URANIUM TARGET,
SLOWED BY TWO 4-CM POLYETHYLENE SLABS PLACED ABOVE
.A LAYER OF U-235 MOUNTED BACK TO BACK WITH A LAYER
OF B-10 IN A LARGE DETECTION CHAMBER
URANIUM LAYER PREPARED BY ELECTROSPRAYING OF
URANYLACETATE ON 0.1 MM AL. ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION
TIME OF FLIGHT AT 30METRE STATION. CHANNEL
DETECTED. ELEMENTAL B-LAYER OF 220 MICRO G/CM*2,
DETECTED. EVAPOURATED LIF OF 176 MICRO G/CM*2,
DATA WERE ALSO NORMALISED TO THE MEASUREMENT OF
DERUYTTER AT LOW ENERGY, SEE JNE 27 645
.CROSS SECTION DATA FROM AUTHORS MAGNETIC TAPE,
OTHER ENERGY INTEGRATED VALUES FROM TABLES IN
RESONANCE TECHNIQUE USING TA,W,MN,MO,CO AND BI.
BACKGROUND CONTRIBUTION VARIED FROM ONE TO SEVERAL
.ERROR ANALYSIS IS ONLY EXPLICITLY GIVEN FOR
ENERGY INTEGRATED VALUES. FLUX RATIO ERROR ABOUT
3 PERCENT, FOR LI NORMALISED DATA PROBABLY NOT
A SYSTEMATIC ERROR OF ONE PERCENT, AND BACKGROUND
UNCERTAINTY CAN REPRESENT UP TO 5 PERCENT IN VALLEYS.
STATISTICAL ACCURACY IS A FEW PARTS PER THOUSAND.
